      • int2ByteEntrySet

        public ObjectSortedSet<Int2ByteMap.Entry> int2ByteEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Int2ByteMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Int2ByteMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
        int2ByteEntrySet in interface Int2ByteMap
        Specified by:
